Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 370
S.P. 162 In Senate, February 3, 2025
Education for a High School Diploma
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on January 30, 2025. Referred to the Committee
on Education and Cultural Affairs pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator LIBBY of Cumberland.
Cosponsored by Representative CARLOW of Buxton and
Senator: RAFFERTY of York, Representatives: BAGSHAW of Windham, HAGGAN of
Hampden, LYMAN of Livermore Falls.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §4722, sub-§2, ¶C, as amended by PL 2019, c. 202, §1, is
3 further amended to read:
4 C. Mathematics--2 3 years or the equivalent in standards achievement;
5 Sec. 2. Department of Education to provide funding. The Department of
6 Education shall provide the necessary funding out of department funds to carry out the
7 purposes of section 1.
8 SUMMARY
99 This bill changes the minimum state standard for mathematics education for a high
1100 school diploma from 2 years of mathematics instruction to 3 years of mathematics
1111 instruction. The bill requires the Department of Education to provide the necessary funding
1122 from department funds to carry out the purposes of the bill.
Page 1 - 132LR0972(01)
